titleStmt.title: Variants of the bound pronoun 2nd person singular masculine after a consonant
titleStmt.author: Veronika Engler

sourceDesc.p: This is the feature-file for the 2nd person singular masculine bound pronoun after a consonant.

revisionDesc.change: For EGY-___ there are no values found

wib:featureValueObservation.note: the vowel here is described to be slightly more fronted than other /a/ sounds following emphatics, but not as fronted as /e/
/-k/ may also succeed liquid, dental or nasal consonants, e.g. baladk `your country`
/-č/ is attested only in the village dialects alongside /-k/
